	<p>Mars Express has been indispensable in the human effort to explore Mars. Though it experienced a fair number of hardships along the way, including the loss of a friend, its journey is one that merits satisfaction and pride. But it isn’t over yet; the orbiter is still fully operational and continues to send data back to us humans on Earth. It’s only 14 years old, a mere teenager, and it has so much more life to experience.</p>

